Author: Mische#6695
Content: How long did it take you to do it @jspook16

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: @Mische so im going to answer that with a caveat. I am familiar with kmd-cli and DNS-setup. It took me about 4 hours. Most of that time was to sync up the kmd chain (i did this on a new server). With the kmd chain synced up, it probably takes 90 minutes. If you are new to kmd-cli and or DNS setup, I think it will take 8 hours. There are tutorials to set up a DNS, tutorials to install komodo, and tutorials to create the asset chain. You do need two instances of komodo running to do this.

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: Once you do it once, creating a new asset chain takes about 15 to 30 mins. Most of that time is deciding what parameters you want to create the chain with.
